<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY">
    <summary>
      <para>Debug message severity levels for an information queue.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Use these values to allow or deny message categories to pass through the storage and retrieval filters for an information queue (see <see cref="D3D11_INFO_QUEUE_FILTER" />). This API is used by <see cref="ID3D11InfoQueue.AddApplicationMessage" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-d3d11-layer-enums">Layer Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY.D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY_CORRUPTION">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines some type of corruption which has occurred.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY.D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY_ERROR">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines an error message.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY.D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY_WARNING">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines a warning message.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY.D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY_INFO">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines an information message.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY.D3D11_MESSAGE_SEVERITY_MESSAGE">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines a message other than corruption, error, warning, or information.</para>
      <para>
        <b>Direct3D 11:  </b>This value is not supported until Direct3D 11.1.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>